commit.message: Fixed lifetime decrement logic so summons actually die after their lifetime runs out.  Thanks katastic!
Fixed directory loading for UNIXes that have /proc
Little changes to fix the build.
Added new build instructions in INSTALL.

Merge pull request #15 from silverhammermba/conflicts

Fix file conflicts with premake4
Merge branch 'master' into conflicts

Merge pull request #14 from silverhammermba/list

Use std::list to replace unit command list.
Use std::list for command linked list
mv loader/parser to not conflict with external libs
Updated libpng, zlib, and cb project.
Made some changes to get an iOS build working properly on the simulator.
Added an Up nav from the Prev button in the campaign picker.  Added some popup dialogs before certain fatal error exits.
Removed fullscreen option from OUYA and Android.
Enabled text block movement controls when USE_CONTROLLER_INPUT is defined.  Still no actual controller support.  That'll take more thought.
Adjusted default settings.  Added Restore Defaults button to options menu.  Added ctrl+F12 hotkey for restoring defaults anytime (e.g. if fullscreen borks up).
Added premake4.lua for premake build system.  Accepts --includedirs, --libdirs, --cflags, and --ldflags.  Make sure you put them on the command line before your premake "ACTION".
Merge remote-tracking branch 'remotes/origin/combat_feedback'
Changed the "starburst"/"hit locations" effect to read as "hit sparks".
Added fix for Android rotation while screen is locked.  Added handling of USE_BMP_SCREENSHOT so I didn't have to mess with the libpng dependency when Android already has a screenshot mechanism.
Merge branch 'combat_feedback' of https://github.com/openglad/openglad into combat_feedback
Changed old blood_friendly to the nicer "poof" version.
Added wrench image for options menu button.
Made an options menu.
Added libpng flag to Linux build target.
Added libpng dependency to enable screenshots (press F10 anywhere).
Added "gore" setting that picks the blood and stain images.  This does not affect any text outside of the level editor.
